com.avaya.jtapi.tsapi

Interface LucentV11AddressListener

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AddressListener, java.util.EventListener

    public interface LucentV11AddressListener
extends AddressListener
    LucentV11AddressListener extends the AddressListener interface with Avaya-specific features. When a Provider is bound to a Avaya Communication Manager switch with PBX Driver Version 11 private data, this interface may be used to access additional capabilities.

    • Method Detail

      • endpointRegistered

        void endpointRegistered(LucentEndpointRegisteredEvent event)
        This method is called to report that an endpoint has registered at this Address. The details of the registered endpoint can be retrieved using the getRegisteredEndpointInfo() method on the LucentEndpointRegisteredEvent class.
        Parameters:
        event - - A LucentEndpointRegisteredEvent with eventID LucentEndpointEvent.ENDPOINT_REGISTERED_EVENT.
        See Also:
        V11RegisteredEndpointInfo

      • endpointUnregistered

        void endpointUnregistered(LucentEndpointUnregisteredEvent event)
        This method is called to report that one of the endpoints registered at this Address has been logged out. The details of the unregistered endpoint can be retrieved using the various methods defined on the LucentEndpointUnregisteredEvent class.
        Parameters:
        event - - A LucentEndpointUnregisteredEvent with eventID LucentEndpointEvent.ENDPOINT_UNREGISTERED_EVENT.
        See Also:
        LucentEndpointUnregisteredEvent
